modules.description: The module enables compression and decompression workflows using zlib or gzip formats, supporting streaming operations with explicit control over headers, dictionaries, and checksums. It operates on Bigarrays and buffers to optimize performance, leveraging strategies like deflate/inflate states and Adler-32 integrity checks for tasks such as network data transmission or archival storage. Key use cases include concurrent data compression pipelines, incremental buffer processing, and verifying data fidelity during decompression.
